## PART 3: RANDOM NUMERICAL VALUE RANGES (EXPANDED)

| Parameter | Symbol | Random Range | Units | Notes |
|-----------|--------|--------------|-------|-------|
| Volume (titration aliquot) | V_aliquot | 10.0 - 50.0 (0.5 increments) | cm³ | |
| Volume (flask/prepared) | V_flask | 100.0 - 500.0 (10 or 25 increments) | cm³ | |
| Concentration (standard) | C_std | 0.01 - 2.00 (2 decimal places) | mol/dm³ | |
| Mass (solid sample) | m_sample | 0.20 - 10.00 (2 decimal places) | g | |
| Titre value | V_titre | 10.0 - 45.0 (0.1 or 0.5 increments) | cm³ | |
| Temperature change | ΔT | **-30.0 to +80.0** (0.1 increments) | °C | **NEGATIVE values for endothermic processes (dissolution of NH₄Cl, etc.)** |
| Volume of gas collected | V_gas | 20 - 500 | cm³ | At r.t.p. (24 dm³/mol) |
| Mass change (thermal decomp) | Δm | 0.10 - 5.00 (2 decimal places) | g | |
| Percentage purity | % | Ask to find | % | |
| Molar mass (given) | M | Calculate from formula | g/mol | Only when RAM toggle is OFF |
| Time (rate experiments) | t | 10 - 300 | s | |
| Activation energy | Ea | 20 - 150 | kJ/mol | |
| Equilibrium constant | Kc | **10⁻²⁰ to 10²⁰** (log scale) | (varies) | **Can be extremely small or extremely large** |
| Initial moles | n | 0.01 - 2.00 | mol | |
| Initial concentrations | [ ] | 0.01 - 2.00 | mol/dm³ | |
| pH value | pH | 0 - 14 | - | Always within 0-14 scale |
| Heat capacity (water) | c | 4.18 | J g⁻¹ K⁻¹ | Constant |
| Density of water | ρ | 1.00 | g cm⁻³ | Constant |
| Heat capacity of calorimeter | C_cal | 10 - 100 | J K⁻¹ | For calorimetry problems |

