## PART 4: REACTION CATEGORIES WITH DETAILED RULES

### A. Acid-Base Titration (Direct)

**Acid Pool:** HCl (strong), HNO₃ (strong), H₂SO₄ (strong), CH₃COOH (weak)
**Base Pool:** NaOH (strong), KOH (strong), Ca(OH)₂ (strong, slightly soluble), NH₃ (weak)
**Indicators:** Select based on acid/base combination:

| Acid | Base | Suitable Indicator | Reason |
|------|------|-------------------|--------|
| Strong | Strong | Methyl orange OR Phenolphthalein | Sharp change at pH 7 |
| Strong | Weak (NH₃) | Methyl orange | Acidic equivalence point (pH < 7) |
| Weak (CH₃COOH) | Strong | Phenolphthalein | Alkaline equivalence point (pH > 7) |
| Weak | Weak | **AVOID** - no sharp endpoint | Not suitable for titration |

**Feasibility Rules:**
- All acids react with all bases
- For H₂SO₄ + Ca(OH)₂ → CaSO₄ is slightly soluble – acceptable for titration
- Ca(OH)₂ is slightly soluble – use saturated solution (~0.02 M) or specify concentration

**Structure A1 (Standard Titration - Find Concentration):**
> "In a titration experiment, a student finds that **[TITRE]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC]** mol/dm³ is required to completely neutralize **[VOLUME]** cm³ of a solution containing **[BASE]** using **[INDICATOR]** as indicator."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]** (if toggle ON: " (Relative atomic masses: H = 1.0, O = 16.0, Na = 23.0, etc.)")
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the concentration of the base solution in mol/dm³ and g/dm³.]*

**Structure A2 (Unknown Acid with Dilution):**
> "A student diluted **[VOLUME]** cm³ of vinegar (containing ethanoic acid) to **[FLASK_VOL]** cm³ in a volumetric flask. **[ALIQUOT]** cm³ of this diluted solution required **[TITRE]** cm³ of **[BASE]** of concentration **[CONC_BASE]** mol/dm³ for neutralization using phenolphthalein indicator."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the original concentration of ethanoic acid in vinegar in mol/dm³ and g/dm³. The pH of the original vinegar was measured to be **[pH_VALUE]** . Comment on whether this pH value is consistent with your calculated concentration.]*

**Structure A3 (Mass of Salt from Titration):**
> "A student titrated **[VOLUME]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC_ACID]** mol/dm³ with **[BASE]** solution of concentration **[CONC_BASE]** mol/dm³. At the endpoint, the solution was evaporated to dryness."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the mass of salt obtained. Identify the salt formed.]*

**Structure A4 (Molar Mass Determination):**
> "A student dissolved **[MASS]** g of an unknown diprotic acid in water and made the solution up to **[FLASK_VOL]** cm³. Titration of **[ALIQUOT]** cm³ of this solution required **[TITRE]** cm³ of **[BASE]** of concentration **[CONC_BASE]** mol/dm³ using phenolphthalein indicator."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]** (if toggle ON: " (Relative atomic masses: H = 1.0, C = 12.0, O = 16.0)")
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the molar mass of the unknown acid.]*

**Structure A5 (Water of Crystallization):**
> "A student dissolved **[MASS]** g of hydrated sodium carbonate (Na₂CO₃·xH₂O) in water and made the solution up to **[FLASK_VOL]** cm³. Titration of **[ALIQUOT]** cm³ of this solution required **[TITRE]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC_ACID]** mol/dm³ using methyl orange indicator."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Determine the value of x in Na₂CO₃·xH₂O.]*

**Structure A6 (pH Calculation from Concentration):**
> "A solution of **[ACID]** has a concentration of **[CONC]** mol/dm³. Assuming complete dissociation for strong acids..."
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the pH of this acid solution.]*

