### B. Acid-Base Titration (Back Titration)

**Use back titration when:**
1. The substance is **insoluble or slightly soluble** (e.g., Mg(OH)₂, CaCO₃, MgO)
2. The reaction is **slow**
3. The endpoint is **difficult to detect directly**
4. The substance is **volatile** (e.g., NH₃)

**Common back titration systems:**

| Substance | Reason for Back Titration | Procedure |
|-----------|--------------------------|-----------|
| Mg(OH)₂ (milk of magnesia) | Slightly soluble, slow reaction | Add excess acid, titrate excess with alkali |
| CaCO₃ (limestone/antacid) | Insoluble, slow with weak acids | Add excess acid, titrate excess |
| MgO | Insoluble base | Add excess acid, titrate excess |
| Ammonium salts | Indirect determination | Add excess NaOH, heat to drive off NH₃, titrate excess |

**Indicator Selection for Back Titration:**
- If excess acid is titrated with strong base → phenolphthalein
- If excess base is titrated with strong acid → methyl orange

**Structure B1 (Insoluble Base/Antacid - Mg(OH)₂, CaCO₃, MgO):**
> "A student crushed an antacid tablet containing **[INSOLUBLE_BASE]** of mass **[MASS]** g and added it to **[VOL_EXCESS]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC_ACID]** mol/dm³. The mixture was warmed to ensure complete reaction. The resulting solution was made up to **[FLASK_VOL]** cm³ in a volumetric flask. A **[ALIQUOT]** cm³ portion of this solution required **[TITRE]** cm³ of **[BASE]** of concentration **[CONC_BASE]** mol/dm³ for neutralization using **[INDICATOR]** indicator."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the percentage by mass of **[INSOLUBLE_BASE]** in the tablet.]*

**Structure B2 (Ammonium Salt Determination - e.g., Fertilizer):**
> "A **[MASS]** g sample of fertilizer containing ammonium sulphate was boiled with **[VOL_EXCESS]** cm³ of **[BASE]** of concentration **[CONC_BASE]** mol/dm³. The ammonia gas evolved was driven off completely. The excess base remaining required **[TITRE]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC_ACID]** mol/dm³ for neutralization using methyl orange indicator."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the percentage of nitrogen in the fertilizer.]*

**Structure B3 (Carbonate in Limestone):**
> "A **[MASS]** g sample of limestone was reacted with **[VOL_EXCESS]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC_ACID]** mol/dm³. After the reaction was complete, the mixture was filtered and the filtrate was made up to **[FLASK_VOL]** cm³. A **[ALIQUOT]** cm³ portion of this solution required **[TITRE]** cm³ of **[BASE]** of concentration **[CONC_BASE]** mol/dm³ for neutralization using **[INDICATOR]** indicator."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the percentage of calcium carbonate in the limestone sample.]*

