### C. Salt Preparation (Soluble) with Limiting Reagent Toggle

**Acid Pool:** HCl, H₂SO₄, HNO₃, CH₃COOH (for slow reactions)
**Base/Metal/Carbonate Pool:** CuO, ZnO, MgO, Mg, Zn, Fe, CaCO₃, Na₂CO₃, K₂CO₃ 

**Feasibility Rules:**
- Acids react with metal oxides, metals (above H), and carbonates
- For metals: Mg, Zn, Fe react with dilute HCl and H₂SO₄ to produce H₂
- For nitric acid with metals: **dilute HNO₃ produces NO, NOT H₂** - specify if gas volume is required
- For ethanoic acid (weak): reacts slowly with metals/carbonates - specify "excess" or "warmed"

**Acid Combinations for Metal Reactions:**
| Metal | With dilute HCl/H₂SO₄ | With dilute HNO₃ | With CH₃COOH |
|-------|----------------------|-------------------|---------------|
| Mg | ✓ H₂ produced | ✓ NO produced (NOT for gas volume) | ✓ Slow reaction |
| Zn | ✓ H₂ produced | ✓ NO produced | ✓ Slow reaction |
| Fe | ✓ H₂ produced | ✓ NO produced | ✓ Slow reaction |
| Cu | ✗ No reaction | ✓ Reacts (oxidizing) | ✗ No reaction |

**Limiting Reagent Toggle:** For structures C2, C3, C4, provide BOTH reactant quantities to require limiting reagent determination.

**Structure C1 (Acid + Insoluble Base - Find Salt Mass):**
> "Excess solid **[SOLID]** is added to **[VOLUME]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC]** mol/dm³. The mixture is heated to complete the reaction, then filtered to remove excess solid. The filtrate is evaporated to dryness."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the maximum mass of anhydrous salt that can be obtained.]*

**Structure C2 (Acid + Metal - with Limiting Reagent):**
> "A student adds **[MASS_METAL]** g of **[METAL]** powder to **[VOLUME_ACID]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC_ACID]** mol/dm³. The hydrogen gas evolved is collected over water at r.t.p."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Determine which reactant is in excess and calculate the volume of hydrogen gas produced at r.t.p. (molar volume = 24 dm³/mol).]*

**Structure C3 (Acid + Carbonate - with Limiting Reagent):**
> "A student adds **[MASS]** g of calcium carbonate to **[VOLUME]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC]** mol/dm³. The carbon dioxide gas produced is collected."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Determine the limiting reagent and calculate the volume of CO₂ produced at r.t.p.]*

**Structure C4 (Acid + Metal Oxide - with Limiting Reagent):**
> "A student adds **[MASS]** g of copper(II) oxide to **[VOLUME]** cm³ of **[ACID]** of concentration **[CONC]** mol/dm³. The mixture is heated until the black solid dissolves completely, forming a blue solution."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Determine the limiting reagent and calculate the mass of copper(II) salt produced. Explain the colour change observed.]*

