### E. Metal Displacement with Reactivity Check

**Reactive Metal Pool:** Zn, Mg, Al, Fe 
**Metal Ion Pool (less reactive):** Cu²⁺ (from CuSO₄/Cu(NO₃)₂), Pb²⁺ (from Pb(NO₃)₂), Ag⁺ (from AgNO₃), Fe²⁺ (from FeSO₄)

**Feasibility Rules - STRICT COMPATIBILITY:**

| Reactive Metal | Can Displace | CANNOT Displace |
|----------------|--------------|------------------|
| Mg | Zn²⁺, Fe²⁺, Pb²⁺, Cu²⁺, Ag⁺ | Ca²⁺, K⁺, Na⁺ |
| Al | Zn²⁺, Fe²⁺, Pb²⁺, Cu²⁺, Ag⁺ | Mg²⁺, Ca²⁺ |
| Zn | Fe²⁺, Pb²⁺, Cu²⁺, Ag⁺ | Mg²⁺, Al³⁺, Ca²⁺ |
| Fe | Pb²⁺, Cu²⁺, Ag⁺ | Zn²⁺, Mg²⁺, Al³⁺, Ca²⁺ |
| Cu | Ag⁺ | All others |

**Common Displacement Reactions:**
- Zn(s) + CuSO₄(aq) → ZnSO₄(aq) + Cu(s) [blue solution fades, brown solid deposits]
- Mg(s) + Pb(NO₃)₂(aq) → Mg(NO₃)₂(aq) + Pb(s)
- Fe(s) + CuSO₄(aq) → FeSO₄(aq) + Cu(s)
- Cu(s) + 2AgNO₃(aq) → Cu(NO₃)₂(aq) + 2Ag(s) [silver crystals form, solution turns blue]

**Structure E1 (Mass of Displaced Metal):**
> "Excess **[REACTIVE_METAL]** powder is added to **[VOLUME]** cm³ of **[METAL_ION_SOURCE]** solution of concentration **[CONC]** mol/dm³. After the reaction is complete, the solid is filtered, washed, dried, and weighed."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the expected mass of **[DISPLACED_METAL]** formed.]*

**Structure E2 (Change in Mass of Metal Strip - with Limiting Reagent):**
> "A strip of **[REACTIVE_METAL]** metal weighing **[INITIAL_MASS]** g is placed into **[VOLUME]** cm³ of **[METAL_ION_SOURCE]** solution of concentration **[CONC]** mol/dm³. After the reaction is complete, the strip is removed, dried, and reweighed."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the final mass of the metal strip.]*

**Structure E3 (Unknown Concentration from Mass Change):**
> "A strip of **[REACTIVE_METAL]** metal weighing **[MASS]** g is placed into **[VOLUME]** cm³ of **[METAL_ION_SOURCE]** solution of unknown concentration. After the reaction, the strip is removed, dried, and found to have a mass of **[FINAL_MASS]** g."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Determine the original concentration of the **[METAL_ION_SOURCE]** solution.]*

**Structure E4 (Colour Change Observation with Calculation):**
> "Excess **[REACTIVE_METAL]** powder is added to **[VOLUME]** cm³ of blue copper(II) sulphate solution of concentration **[CONC]** mol/dm³. The mixture is stirred until the blue colour disappears completely."
> 
> **[RAM_INFO]**
> 
> *[Task: Calculate the mass of copper solid produced. Explain the colour change observed and write the ionic equation for the reaction.]*

