### F. Redox Titration

**Oxidizing Agent Pool:** KMnO₄ (acidified), K₂Cr₂O₇ (acidified), I₂ 
**Reducing Agent Pool:** FeSO₄, Na₂SO₃, H₂O₂, H₂C₂O₄ (ethanedioic acid), KI, Na₂S₂O₃ (for iodine titrations)

**Feasibility Rules:**

| Oxidizing Agent | Works With | Reaction Type | Indicator |
|-----------------|------------|---------------|-----------|
| KMnO₄ (acidified) | Fe²⁺ → Fe³⁺, C₂O₄²⁻ → CO₂, SO₃²⁻ → SO₄²⁻, H₂O₂ → O₂ | Purple to colourless | Self-indicating |
| K₂Cr₂O₇ (acidified) | Fe²⁺ → Fe³⁺, SO₃²⁻ → SO₄²⁻ | Orange to green | Diphenylamine or self-indicating |
| I₂ | S₂O₃²⁻ → S₄O₆²⁻, SO₃²⁻ → SO₄²⁻ | Brown to colourless | Starch (blue-black → colourless) |

