### G. Metal Reaction with Acid (Gas Volume)

**Metal Pool:** Mg, Zn, Fe, Al 
**Acid Pool:** HCl (dilute), H₂SO₄ (dilute), CH₃COOH (dilute - weak)

**Feasibility Rules:**
- Mg, Zn, Fe react with dilute HCl and H₂SO₄ to produce H₂ gas
- Al reacts but may require initial oxide layer removal
- Metals above H in reactivity series ONLY
- Cu, Ag, Au DO NOT react with dilute acids
- **Very dilute HNO₃** can react with some metals but produces NO, NOT H₂ - NOT suitable for gas volume calculations
- CH₃COOH (weak acid) reacts slowly - specify "excess" or "warmed"

**Structure G1 (Gas Volume from Metal Mass):**
